item.description:
Origin of &ldquo;Old Kukis&rdquo; vs &ldquo;New Kukis&rdquo;
Old Kukis (Nagas, Komrems and some Kukis like Gangtes) =/= New Kukis (Thadou, Paite, Hmar, etc). Kuki militants were attacking Koms not long ago.
Old Kukis were brought in by Meitei kings to act as counter against Nagas only around 16th century. Mizos arrived into Mizoram only in 19th-20th century as recorded by the British. Kukis started arriving into Manipur from around 17th century.
